Root cause

The only pending pod is:

bscf181-pmp0-b755b55b9-8w4n2
STATUS: Pending

The node shows:

Allocatable CPU : 108
Requested CPU   : 103.862
Remaining       : ~4.138 CPUs

From your earlier deployment, PMP0 requests 5 CPUs.

Since only about 4.1 CPUs are available, the scheduler reports:

0/1 nodes are available: 1 Insufficient cpu

Why oc adm top node shows only 13% CPU

This is expected.

oc adm top node shows actual CPU usage (currently ~14 cores).

The scheduler uses CPU requests, not current usage.


A pod requesting 5 CPUs reserves those CPUs even if it's currently using only a fraction of them.

Verify PMP0 request

Run:

oc describe pod bscf181-pmp0-b755b55b9-8w4n2

or

oc get pod bscf181-pmp0-b755b55b9-8w4n2 -o jsonpath='{.spec.containers[*].resources.requests.cpu}'

It should show a request of 5 CPUs.

Options to resolve

1. Reduce PMP0 CPU request (if the BSCF application supports it).


2. Free at least 1 more CPU request by reducing another workload's request or scaling something down.


3. Increase node CPU capacity if the hardware supports additional cores.



